2026-04-16 12:15:08 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 3'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that in Control Module 3 the continuity between the input (+) terminal and the switch is open‑circuit, while the path from the switch to the output (+) terminal is intact and the 0 V line is continuous. Consequently the +12 V from upstream never reaches either the switch or the indicator LED / resistor branch, so module 3’s LED is off and the series chain to the load is interrupted. This single internal open on the + input side of Control Module 3 explains why only the first two control indicators light and the lamp never turns on even when all switches are ON. Replacing or repairing Control Module 3 should restore the system.'
